## How to Run

### Step 1 — Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 2 — Download the dataset
- Go to [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shivamb/real-or-fake-fake-jobpostings)
- Download `fake_job_postings.csv`
- Place it in `dataset/` folder

### Step 3 — Run the Notebook
Open `notebook/internship_detection.ipynb` in Jupyter or Google Colab → **Run All Cells**

### Step 4 — CLI Prediction tool
```bash
python app/prediction_script.py
```

### Step 5 — Web App (Optional)
```bash
streamlit run app/streamlit_app.py
```

---

## What the Notebook Covers (16 Cells)

| Cell | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| 1 | Install & import all libraries |
| 2 | Load dataset from CSV |
| 3 | Explore dataset (info, value counts, missing values) |
| 4 | **Visualization** — Fake vs Legitimate bar & pie chart |
| 5 | **Preprocessing** — Fill nulls, remove duplicates |
| 6 | **Feature Engineering** — Merge text columns → `text_data` |
| 7 | **NLP** — `clean_text()` function (lowercase, remove stopwords/URLs/HTML) |
| 8 | **TF-IDF** — Vectorize text into 10,000 features |
| 9 | **Train-Test Split** — 80/20 with stratification |
| 10 | **Train 4 Models** — LR, Naive Bayes, Random Forest, SVM |
| 11 | **Classification Reports** for all models |
| 12 | **Visualization** — Grouped bar + horizontal accuracy chart |
| 13 | **Confusion Matrices** — 2×2 grid for all models |
| 14 | **Save best model** to `models/trained_model.pkl` |
| 15 | **Prediction System** — `predict_internship()` function + 4 test cases |
| 16 | Interactive prediction cell |

